# Freshdesk Reviews 2025: The Good, the Bad, and the Ugly
## Introduction
Freshdesk is a popular customer support software known for its strong ticketing system, live chat, SLA, and multi-channel support. This review will break down what customers love about Freshdesk, where it might fall short, and provide a well-rounded view to help businesses make the right decision.

## Features
Freshdesk offers a range of features, including:
* Ticketing system
* Reporting and analytics
* Automation and workflow management
* Customization
* Customer support

## Pricing
Freshdesk offers a 21-day free trial and several pricing plans:
* Free plan for up to 10 agents
* Growth plan ($15/agent/month)
* Pro plan ($49/agent/month)
* Enterprise plan ($79/agent/month)

Customers have mixed opinions about Freshdesk's pricing:
> Freshdesk can be expensive, especially for small businesses with limited budgets.
> The pricing structure of Freshdesk also leaves much to be desired.

## Ticketing System
Freshdesk's ticketing system is designed to streamline customer support by providing a centralized platform for managing all incoming queries. Customers praise its ease of use and ability to add features through the marketplace. However, some users see room for improvement in its automation, specifically the need for an automated system to merge similar tickets.

## Reporting and Analytics
Freshdesk offers a comprehensive reporting and analytics tool suite, but customers have found the new analytics system to be overly complex and limited in its customization options.

## Automation and Workflow Management
Freshdesk's automation and workflow management features are designed to streamline customer support processes and enhance efficiency. Customers appreciate its ability to automate repetitive tasks and integrate with third-party apps.

## Customization
Freshdesk offers a range of customization options, but customers have found its customization options limited, making it challenging to fully personalize the software to meet their unique needs.

## Customer Support
Freshdesk's customer support has received mixed feedback from users, with some praising its multi-channel support and knowledge base, while others have found the setup process painful and the ongoing support slow.

## Overall Customer Satisfaction
Customer satisfaction with Freshdesk is mixed, with many users appreciating its ease of use and features, but others finding its pricing and customization options limited.

## Alternatives
Alternatives to Freshdesk include Desk365, which offers a range of features, including AI agent, automations, SLAs, and customization options, at a lower price point.

## Conclusion
Freshdesk is a robust customer support software with a range of features, but its pricing and customization options may be limiting for some businesses. Alternatives like Desk365 may offer more affordable and flexible solutions for customer support needs.